     FTP, or File Transfer Protocol, is the primary method of uploading and
     downloading files on the web. In this short course, Scott Simpson helps
     you understand how essential FTP is to users and the administrators who
     support them, and shows how to connect to FTP servers from the command
     line, a client, or a browser. Scott also explains how to transfer data
     more securely using SFTP.
